      "stem_html": "<p>Treatment of a cyclic ketone with diazomethane is a method for accomplishing a ring-expansion reaction. For example, treatment of cyclohexanone with diazomethane yields cycloheptanone. Propose a mechanism.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBaGNZIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--274a5eb8cb1ec6c9f18913a0e234bc3de7d2edaf/OChem_22_EC_025.jpg\" alt=\"Cyclohexanone reacts with diazomethane in ether to yield cycloheptanone and molecular nitrogen as the products.\">",
